Associated Press (2005) Among the Military Child Education Coalition's successes was an agreement in 2000 by the Army and Air Force to allow soldiers and airmen to stay in one place when they have children entering their senior year, except for wartime combat assignments.↩
Recent studies, however, have shown that mobility during the school year may be less traumatic than summer time moves. Ender (1996) P 145. &lt;U+201C&gt;Despite the commonly held belief that summer moves are best for children, teens who moved during summer vacation seemed to experience particular difficulties&lt;U+2026&gt; Their problem was that, with school out of session, it was very difficult to identify potential friends and begin to form relationships.&quot; Tyler (2002) p 27.↩

